# gen177 — B5 locals: parrot0 tracks a writable environment of local variables —
# declarations (int x = expr;), reassignments (x = x + 10;), assignment to a
# parameter — and uses them in later expressions and returns, alongside branches.
#expect: pass
#faculty: symeval-locals
> what does f(3) return: int f(int n) { int x = n * 2; return x + 1; }
< f(3) returns 7
> what does g(5) return: int g(int n) { int x = n; x = x + 10; return x; }
< g(5) returns 15
> what does area(3, 4) return: int area(int w, int h) { int a = w * h; int b = a + 1; return b; }
< area(3, 4) returns 13
> what does clamp(15) return: int clamp(int n) { int m = n; if (m > 10) { return 10; } return m; }
< clamp(15) returns 10
